Assam proposes denying govt jobs for those with over 2 kids.
A draft population policy of the Assam government has suggested that people with more than two children will be denied government jobs. The draft also said that all girls of the state will be given free education up to university. Briefing media in state capital, Assam's Health Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma said that this is a draft population policy and that they have suggested that people having more than two children will not be eligible for any government jobs."This is a draft population policy. We have suggested that people having more than two children will not be eligible for any government jobs," Biswa Sarma said.